**Edit**<br>
<br>
Reason why? I liked the idea of calendar system when I played on the Rathe. I was instrumental in creating the system that is currently used. However the RTA (Rathe Travel Agency) no longer even remotely resembles what I helped to create. I see the *exact* same thing happening here that happened there. The calendar system you have will follow one of two paths. <br>
<br>
A)Do nothing and the system will self destruct eventually anyway do to more and more people reaching the +46 level game and demanding there time in the planes. People will stop posting intent and stat going FFA, while some will hang on for dear life claiming a &quot;Right&quot; to any calendar mob/plane they have posted for.<br>
<br>
or you (admins)will try and make it work<br>
<br>
B)You will first adapt the system by allowing only one post per raid per guild. (IE you cant post another raid to fear until you've completed your first one, but you can post any other plane raid so long as you have no other pending date for that plane).  Then you'll extend the post time to one month instead of 2 weeks so that the 40+ guilds all wanting to go to the plane wont be Midnight camping the calendar to try and get there raid in before anyone else, which inevitably leads to the Rants and Raves forum exploding with injustices of ever sort. Then youll you'll start limiting access to the calendar. Requiring that a guild have 40+ planable members. Then the indies will kick up there rants till you make a rule allowing alliances to to post as long as they have 40+ members that are 46+, BUT anyone in an alliance that is part of a posting guild cant be counted towards the final number AND you cant have more than 6 people from any one posting guild / alliance part of another alliance. This is to prevent guilds from piggy backing each other into the planes (Get us on yours we'll get you on ours kinda of thing) because by this time you have to wait about a month and half between each plane raid. At this point the system is starting to bulge at the seems with dedicated admins rotating in and out every three months because the system is such a pain in the ASS to maintain administratively. Then comes the Big Brother guilds. If your in fear with your 40+ raiding party and you cant take down Cazic Thule who just so happened to pop on your raid, you arent allowed to call in any sister guild, or friend guild, you have to call in The Desiganted Big Brother Guild. To become a &quot;BB guild&quot; as it was know you had to be able to clear to the 6th Isle in Air I believe (Cant remember anymore), then you were tagged a &quot;BB guild&quot;. BB guild's rotated spawns and kept the record straight between themsleves, so that if BB guild A killed Cazic yesterday, and Inny just popped today then it was BB guild B's turn and so on. You as the raid leader of whatever plane had to call the BB guild by 10pm PST I think it was, if you didnt think you could kill the god. This was of course to ensure nothing went to waste and maximum spawn times per year were achieved. The amazing thing about it all, this was just for planes. Now try adding mobs to the mix! LOL no thx plz.<br>
<br>
I left the above system behind to other admins, about the time they made calendar access protected with a password, so that the admins could verify your claim to a 40+ guild/alliance. I then left the server entirely for crowding reasons and came to this server. If you want to check out this marvel of red tape and headaches go here <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://boh.thixo.net/">boh.thixo.net/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
To the Admins:<br>
Do yourselves a favor. Delete the calendar now before it grows out of control.</font><P><p align="center"><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=42793" target="_blank"><img src="http://gucomics.everlore.com/coolstuff/sigpic_01.jpg" border="0"><br>
